title: For Sale:  .02
postcontent:
ARMSLIST and all other gun marketplaces are community run for the most part. As a gun community we need to come together to rid ourselves of one of the deadliest sins - greed. We are all tired of seeing $500 AK-47s listed at $2000, and $800 fully upgraded AR-15s posted for $4500. Guess what? As gun buyers and members on this and other forums, we are just as responsible for the state of our society as the price gougers and hoarders. We need to come together and do two thing: (1) STOP BUYING AT THESE RIDICULOUS PRICES and (2) click on the ad, go to "Flag" at the top, and press "overpriced." This whole process takes 1.3968 seconds.

These price criminals only have business if someone is ignorant enough to buy and if they spread their advertisement. NOTE TO GUN COMMUNITY: Guns aren't going anywhere. Ammo isn't going anywhere. Magazines are the biggest threat of changing but let's face it, do we really need 100 round drums or is that more of a want? Every time you skip over a $10,000 ad for a $3000 purchased SCAR 17, you have just became part of the problem. Send them a hate email showing the prices before hoarding and then promptly flag their ad so we can get prices back under the 1000s where they all belong. For the uninformed or misinformed audience, I have put together a short list of reasonable prices for standard guns. What I am asking is that everyone read this post and then immediately copy and paste it to another state's listing in the US. Add your own two cents in if you'd like or if I got anything wrong. The regularity will only return if we make it.

AR-15: $600-$1300 depending on brand and usage (shots fired, wear, etc..)
AK-47: $400-$900
SKS:$300-$500
SCAR 16/17: $2000/$2800
AR-10: $1000-1500
Glock: $400-600
10/22: $229
ACR: $2000
1911: $600-1100
9mm ammo: $0.25/round is on the higher end
223/5.56: $0.35/round
.308/7.62 NATO: maybe up to $1/round (on high side)
.22: $0.05/round is high

Again, feel free to add your $0.02, make changes, repost, and then get to the flagging of overpriced scams.

This handgun was inspired by the infamous Wiley Clapp and is therefore known as the "Wiley Clapp Edition". These guns are designed specifically as a DEFENSE/ COMBAT .357 and as such have many features not found on the standard GP100's.
This revolver features a 3 inch full underlug barrel (which in my humble opinion is the MINIMUM barrel length necessary for tapping into the .357 magnums power).  It also has low profile and snag free NOVAK sights factory installed.
The Standard GP100 in the 3 in. model does not come with a rear sight. This model comes with a dovetailed Novak Front and Rear sight.   The Front sight has the highly visible fiber optic rod for quick target acquisition. 
***These dovetailed sights allow the user to replace the front and rear sights with TRIJICON Tritium nights sights or some other variant of night sight***.  
The standard GP100 has a reflective stainless finish. This gun has a specialized non-reflective matte finish called the "Hawkeye finish". These are just a few of the UPGRADES made only to this model GP100. Please see the specs listed below as taken from Ruger's website:

Material: Stainless Steel Finish: Matte Stainless
Front Sight: Fiber Optic Novak Rear Sight: Lo-Mount Novak
Barrel Length: 3.00" Overall Length: 8.50"
Weight: 36.00 oz. Grips: Black Rubber
Twist: 1:18.75" RH Grooves: 5
Capacity: 6 Avalable From: TALO

This revolver is Like New in box (as I am the original owner and fired less than 25 INCREDIBLY accurate rounds through it). It comes with EVERYTHING as new, including paperwork, fired casing, lock, and Ruger Plastic Box. Get this AWESOME revolver without a wait and the soon to be MANDATORY paper TRAIL...... This revolver is considerably light weight (only 36 oz.) for an all stainless gun that is designed for a lifetime of the hottest .357 rounds. This revolver is considered a Limitted edition and as such, these are investments that will only increase in value. I am not thrilled to let it go.... but need to fund other things...
Please feel free to contact me with any questions you may have.
$875 or Best Offer
Thanks for Looking!

title: For Sale:  1939 Mosin Nagant *Pristine* collector item w/ 500 rounds
postcontent:
Up for sale or possible trade is this 1939, pre World War II, Russian Mosin Nagant Model 91/30.  This Mosin is in such incredible condition.  Just but a few years ago it was pulled from stock in Russia and sent to the states to be sold as surplus.  It is so unused that it is STILL full of grease.  So I guess the only down side is that you have to disassemble and clean out all the packing grease.  It comes with bayonet, cleaning kits, and sling, all original to the weapon and in perfect condition - no marks, scratches, etc.

  In addition to this prestine weapon, I also have a ammo can full of brand new 7.62x54r ammunition for the Mosin.  This is not surplus ammo, it is brand new.  Approximately 450-500 rounds.  Do the math...20 rounds of this ammo at Academy or Cabela's runs approximately $23.99.  If you round down to $1.00 a round, that means that there are approximately $450.00 - $500.00 is prestine ammunition included for this weapon...when rounded down. 

  I am open to trades, however they must be of equal or more value, please don't waste yours or my time.  I am always interested in trades outside of firearms as well, just let me know what you have. The price to start is $600 obo, this is negotiable within reason.  I know you may think that this is a lot but please take a look at other Mosin Nagants on the web.  They're usually not even close to the condition this is, they're not pre World War II (they're usually 1943 and 1946), do not come with all the accessories, are not as unused, and definitely don't come with 450-500 rounds of NEW ammunition....

I am in the military and currently stationed in texas, I will be driving all of my firearms and vehicle home to maryland for storage before I leave to go back overseas, I will sell the mosin at that time. It should be within the first or second week of may. This is for serious individuals only. Please do not waste my time. I am not hardpressed for sale as this would be a great heirloom to hand down when I have children old enough, by that time this will be close to 100 years old. Email me for a quick response
